			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	About Us:</p>
<p>
	As one of the fastest growing social advertising platforms, GLO Gaming is dedicated to helping Fortune 500 brands in achieving their paid digital media objectives by leveraging the highly-performing nature of incentive-based advertising, both in-game and on top comscore sites.</p>
<p>
	Headquartered in NewYork, New York, GLO Gaming is a privately held, highly profitable and well-funded company. Through extensive relationships with game, application, and lifestyle publishers, GLO offers brands unique opportunities to place their campaigns in front of the growing audience of social gamers and hungry virtual currency seekers. GLO Gaming is seeking experienced, passionate and self-motivated Account Executives in the New York, Los Angeles, and Chicago markets.</p>
<p>
	Responsibilities:</p>
<p>
	&bull; Leverage existing relationships with senior level decision makers and influencers in prospective regions to develop new relationships, penetrate new accounts and drive new business.</p>
<p>
	&bull; Build high-level agency and client relationships that translate into recurring business</p>
<p>
	&bull; Identify potential sales prospects</p>
<p>
	&bull; Promote the GLO brand, and help stimulate advertising demand in your sales territory</p>
<p>
	&bull; Create persuasive sales presentations using market trends, case studies and social network (primarily Facebook) marketing solutions</p>
<p>
	&bull; Exceed client meeting, RFP and sales goals</p>
<p>
	&bull; Work with sales planners to execute and deliver high quality answers to all RFP&rsquo;s</p>
<p>
	&bull; Ability to prioritize and deliver timely work</p>
<p>
	&bull; Ability to provide scalable solutions and strategies in a rapid growth and changing environment</p>
<p>
	Requirements:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		2+ years of digital media sales experience with a proven track record of meeting and exceeding sales quotas; we do welcome seasoned Account Managers who are ready to move up to an AE role</li>
	<li>
		4yr college degree from an accredited university</li>
	<li>
		Expansive rolodex of current and positive business relationships with the top media agencies including Mindshare, Mediacom, MEC, Starcom, MediaVest, Carat, Horizon, Draft, OMD, Digitas, UM, Hill Holiday etc</li>
	<li>
		Exceptional organizational skills and the ability to self-motivate.</li>
	<li>
		Excellent communication, relationship management and presentation skills</li>
	<li>
		Must have a demonstrated proficiency in strategic advertising solutions, thoughtful presentations, skillful negotiating and deal-closing</li>
	<li>
		High level knowledge and experience selling video and/or in-game advertising a plus</li>
	<li>
		Intimate knowledge of online media space and the ability to execute on a long-term sales strategy in your region</li>
	<li>
		Recognizable industry presence and proven track record of success driving revenue through the development of long-term strategic relationships</li>
	<li>
		Demonstrated track record of structuring and managing complex negotiations to successful closure and delivery</li>
	<li>
		Ability to act as an evangelist at an industry level for social media marketing</li>
	<li>
		Understand social network (e.g. Facebook) user behavior, how the technology works and the ability to explain each in ordinary terms</li>
</ul>
